title: truffle console: SyntaxError: Unexpected identifier
body:
Truffle migrate is working good but while running truffle console

- SyntaxError: Unexpected identifier
    at new Script (vm.js:51:7)
    at createScript (vm.js:136:10)
    at Object.runInContext (vm.js:181:10)
    at Console.interpret (C:\Users\labo\AppData\Roaming\npm\node_modules\truffle\build\cli.bundled.js:106593:17)
    at ReplManager.interpret (C:\Users\labo\AppData\Roaming\npm\node_modules\truffle\build\cli.bundled.js:107310:18)
    at bound (domain.js:375:14)
    at REPLServer.runBound [as eval] (domain.js:388:12)
    at REPLServer.onLine (repl.js:492:10)
    at REPLServer.emit (events.js:180:13)
    at REPLServer.emit (domain.js:421:20)
## Environment

* Operating System: Windows
* Ethereum client:
* Truffle version (`truffle version`):v4.1.6
* node version (`node --version`):v9.9.0
* npm version (`npm --version`): 5.8.0

@vidhyaramani Hi. Within `truffle console` you don't need to prefix the commands with `truffle`. To migrate, just type `migrate`.  There's a list of available commands [here](http://truffleframework.com/docs/getting_started/console#commands-available).

Could you check to see if removing the word 'truffle' from your command solves this problem?
no its not working still. Could you explain me how to deploy the smart contract? steps to do it  after truffle migrate. Thanks!

@vidhyaramani Are you still seeing this syntax error after making the change suggested? If so could provide steps to reproduce it?

`truffle-migrate` deploys the the contract. Please see the truffle documentation [here](http://truffleframework.com/docs/getting_started/migrations#running-migrations) for more.

@vidhyaramani You are seeing this message: `SyntaxError: Unexpected identifier` after running `migrate` in truffle console? Please list steps to reproduce the error you're seeing, including the output you see in your terminal.

@vidhyaramani I see the error you're describing when I do this:
```
truffle console
truffle(development)> truffle migrate
```

Error goes away when I do this:
```
truffle console
truffle(development)> migrate
```

Same error is coming so it's not deploying the  coding..please need to get rid of this.thanks!

```
truffle unbox metacoin
```

```
module.exports = {
  networks: {
    development: {
      host: "127.0.0.1",
      port: 8545,
      network_id: "*" // Match any network id
    }
  }
};
```
In a second terminal tab launch the client:
```
ganache-cli
```

truffle console --network development

@vidhyaramani I'm going to close this issue I'm sorry. I would advise you to read through the [documentation](http://truffleframework.com/docs/) and familiarize yourself with the plaform, following each step in a tutorial. We have some available on the site. The GitHub issues are for bug reports and feature requests and it looks like your initial report about the syntax error is not what's at issue here anymore.
You cannot use the truffle keyword when you are in truffle develop
